    div#projects
        div.info-card
            div.project-media 
                img(src="/images/dashboard.png", alt="Dashboard visualizations")
            div.project-entry 
                h1 Spokane Economic Recovery Dashboard (W.I.P.)
                p 
                | Our project aims at providing a user-friendly experience for a set of Economic indicators provided by our sponsor, Greater Spokane Inc. The 
                | dashboard is meant to provide the citizens of Spokane and those who may plan on moving here a detailed set of visualizations pertaining to 
                | the current state of the greater Spokane area's economy, updating as new data becomes available. The dashboard will serve as a means for those 
                | interested in learning more about Spokane's economy to obtain a greater understanding of both the current state of affairs but also the 
                | direction the area is headed pertaining to real estate and economic indicators.
                p 
                | Our application is built using Node.js, Express.js, and Python and the application is hosted on Heroku. The application is supported using a 
                | MongoDB backend database for storing key economic indicator data. Full project plan can be found on the GitHub repository and the Google Drive
                | documents.
                div.button-container
                    button(onclick="location.href='https://spokaneeconomicdashboard.herokuapp.com'") Project Site
                    button(onclick="location.href='https://github.com/zfoteff/gu-cs07'") GitHub Project 
                    button(onclick="location.href='https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1BNPNeB3jtIR3Glxu65ILHqAECRiTyKqQ'") Google Drive Arcitecture Documents
        div.info-card
            div.project-media
                video(src="/images/LEDDemo.mp4" controls) 
            div.project-entry 
                h1 Sound Reactive LED System
                p 
                | While at college, I was inspired by a classmate to create a sound reactive LED light system after I learned about how exorbitantly expensive 
                | those systems can be. Using an Arduino Uno, a three meter LED strip, and
                | a parallax sound impact sensor I was able to create a system that pulses when the ambient sound in the room exceeds certain decibel threshold.
                p
                | I am currently working on a new iteration that uses an addressable LED strip, which will allow for greater customization
                | and more light sequences. Additionally, I am trying to integrate a new sensor that is more sensitive to changes in decibel levels, 
                | which will also allow for greater customization.
                p 
                | For this project I learned these new skills:               
                ul
                    li Using Arduino micro controllers
                    li Manipulating addressable LED strips
                    li Creating hardware schematics and wiring components
                    li Soldering
                div.button-container
                    button(onclick="location.href='https://github.com/zfoteff/SoundReactiveLED'") GitHub Project
