        div.info-card
            div.project-media 
                video(src="/images/JumpShotDemo.mp4" alt="Jump Shot Demo Video" controls)
            div.project-entry 
                h1 Jump-Shot (Android Application)
                p 
                | This Android application was created as my final project for Android App Development at Gonzaga University.
                | The intent of the application is to allow users to  create an application that allows fans at sporting events to pool 
                | their photos together to create a fan-created compilation of the best moments at the game. 
                p
                | Fans have the capability to upload photos and videos 
                | to game specific channels and save photos from the game. the game specific channels are viewable using a Google maps plugin overlaid 
                | with waypoints over the locations of recent games. The application isn't limited to sporting events, the application can be used for other 
                | large events where fans may want to compile their photos together.
                div.button-container
                    button(onclick="location.href='https://github.com/zfoteff/JumpShot'") GitHub Project
        div.info-card
            div.project-media 
                img(src="/images/notestorelogin.png", alt="Note Store - Login Screen")
                img(src="/images/notestorehomescreen.png", alt="Note Store - Home Screen")
            div.project-entry 
                h1 Note Store: Encrypted Notetaking Application 
                p 
                | I created a web app that allows users to not only create notes, but also create sections of notes and save notes as .txt files or in 
                | MongoDB. Users can create separate accounts with their own segregated notes and documents. Users can login to their account, create new 
                | notes, and upload/download files in their repositories. Each user's documents will be encrypted with their own private key so only they 
                | will be able to access their own documents.
                div.button-container
                    button(onclick="location.href='https://github.com/zfoteff/Note-Store'") GitHub Project
        div.info-card
            div.project-media 
                img(src="/images/flappy.png" alt="Flappy Bird Screenshot")
            div.project-entry
                h1 Flappy Bird
                p
                | I recreated the popular mobile game Flappy Bird using handmade pixel art and the Pygame module. 
                | The game follows a simple loop where the player tries to navigate between the pipes and survive as long as they can. 
                | Future iterations will involve a scoring system, as well as more dynamic animations.
                p 
                | For this project I learned these new skills:
                ul
                    li Using the PyGame Python library
                    li Manipulating sprite models 
                    li Infite scrolling 
                    li Creating pixel art
                div.button-container
                    button(onclick="location.href='https://github.com/zfoteff/fuppy_birb'") GitHub Link
        div.info-card       
            div.project-media
                img(src="/images/cways.png" alt="Conway's Game of Life Screenshot")
            div.project-entry
                h1 Conway's Game of Life
                p
                | Using Python, I created a command line implementaion of Conway's Game of Life
                | The game is referred to as a "celluar automaton" that models cell growth in generations based off of 4 rules:
                ol
                    li All cells with one or no neighbors die 
                    li All cells with 4 or more neighbors die 
                    li All cells with two or three neighbors survives to the next generation 
                    li All dead cells with exactly 4 neighbors are resurrected in the next generation
                p
                | Each time the program is started a randomly generated colony of cells is created, acting as the initial state for the colony to evolve from. The
                | player then can observe the colony evolve each generation following the four rules. 
                p 
                | Future versions may include: a GUI that allows for better user control and the option to input custom initial colonies.
                div.button-container
                    button(onclick="location.href='https://github.com/zfoteff/cways_life'") GitHub Project Link 
                    button(onclick="location.href='https://bitstorm.org/gameoflife/'") Original Source